ODM has gazetted names of party officials who were appointed in changes unveiled during a special executive council meeting in February. The over 15 names were published by the Registrar of Political Parties Lucy Ndung'u in a notice dated April 25. In the notice, the party has listed Edwin Sifuna the substantive Secretary General replacing Ababu Namwamba (now Foreign Affairs CAS) who resigned in July 2016. Governors Hassan Joho (Mombasa) and Wycliffe Oparanya (Kakamega) will serve as deputy party leaders while National Assembly Minority Leader John Mbadi (Suba South) will remain the national chairman. Turkana Governor Josphat Nanok, who is Council of Governors chairman, was appointed Vice Chairperson alongside Janet Ongera who replaces Paul Otuoma. Thomas Mwadeghu has officially taken over from Adan Keynan and Christine Lemein. More on appointments: Raila replaces ex-Secretary General Ababu Namwamba with Edwin Sifuna Related: Nasa troubles a case of 'normal sibling rivalry', says Raila "In exercise of the power conferred by section 20 (1) (c) of the Political Parties Act, 2011, the Registrar of Political Parties gives notice that Orange Democratic Movement intends to change its party officials," Ndung'u said. She asked those with written submissions concerning the intended change by the political party to deposit the same with the registrar within seven days. Click here for the latest political news    